0115%20methane%20emissions%20over%20the%20six%20months%20of%20the%20Kazakh%20leak%2C%20their%20analysis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Kazakh%20leak%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20disastrous%20ever%20recorded%2C%20according%20to%20Luis%20Guanter%20of%20the%20Polytechnic%20University%20of%20Valencia%2C%20who%20was%20part%20of%20the%20research%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20the%20BBC%20that%20%26quot%3Bonly%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnord-stream-pipelines-attacked-remote-explosives-uk-intelligence-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENord%20Stream%20sabotage%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20have%20led%20to%20a%20stronger%20leak.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuzachi%20Neft%2C%20the%20operator%20of%20the%20well%2C%20denied%20to%20the%20outlet%20that%20such%20a%20vast%20amount%20of%20methane%20was%20leaked%2C%20saying%20only%20a%20%26quot%3Bnegligible%26quot%3B%20amount%20was%20released.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuzachi%20Neft%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmethane-spill-released-year-worth-gas-cars-kazakhstan-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708062464000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ceeb916fcb546d2d507f03%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmethane-spill-released-year-worth-gas-cars-kazakhstan-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20well%20leak%2C%20which%20lasted%20from%20June%20to%20December%202023%2C%20is%20estimated%20to%20have%20released%20140%2C000%20tons%20of%20methane%20into%20Earth's%20atmosphere.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmethane-spill-released-year-worth-gas-cars-kazakhstan-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kim%20Jong%20Un's%20Powerful%20Sister%20Offers%20Rare%20Olive%20Branch%20To%20Japan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20influential%20sister%20of%20North%20Korean%20leader%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20offered%20a%20rare%20opening%20for%20Japan%2C%20saying%20she%20saw%20a%20positive%20tone%20in%20comments%20from%20Prime%20Minister%20Fumio%20Kishida%2C%20who%20is%20seeking%20a%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKim%20Yo%20Jong%20indicated%20a%20meeting%20of%20leaders%20would%20be%20possible%20if%20Japan%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20lay%20such%20a%20stumbling%20block%20as%20the%20already%20settled%20abduction%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20a%20press%20statement%20issued%20Thursday%20on%20state%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20my%20opinion%20that%20if%20Japan%20makes%20a%20political%20decision%20to%20open%20up%20a%20new%20way%20of%20mending%20the%20relations%20through%20its%20courteous%20behavior%20and%20trustworthy%20action%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20courageously%20breaking%20with%20anachronistic%20hostility%20and%20unattainable%20desire%20and%20recognizing%20each%20other%2C%20the%20two%20countries%20can%20open%20up%20a%20new%20future%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20carried%20on%20the%20Korean%20Central%20News%20Agency%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tone%20is%20a%20marked%20change%20from%20comments%20she%20issued%20nearly%20two%20years%20ago%20when%20she%20lumped%20Japan%20in%20a%20bunch%20of%20%26quot%3Bsinister%26quot%3B%20nations%20she%20accused%20of%20raising%20rabble%20at%20the%20United%20Nations%20to%20criticize%20Pyongyang%20for%20the%20test%20of%20an%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile.%20She%20has%20also%20unleashed%20speeches%20with%20fiery%20and%20threatening%20language%20directed%20at%20South%20Korea's%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJapan's%20top%20government%20spokesman%2C%20Yoshimasa%20Hayashi%2C%20said%20Friday%20that%20Tokyo%20was%20taking%20note%20of%20the%20comments%20from%20Kim%20Yo%20Jong.%20He%20also%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Btotally%20unacceptable%26quot%3B%20to%20consider%20the%20abduction%20issue%20as%20resolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20nearly%20impossible%20for%20Kishida%20not%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20abductee%20issue%2C%20which%20has%20played%20a%20prominent%20role%20in%20the%20priorities%20of%20his%20ruling%20Liberal%20Democratic%20Party%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20North%20Korea%20appears%20to%20be%20warming%20up%20slightly%20to%20Japan%2C%20it%20has%20widened%20a%20chasm%20between%20itself%20and%20Seoul.%20Last%20week%2C%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20said%20he%20has%20the%20legal%20right%20to%20annihilate%20South%20Korea%2C%20in%20his%20latest%20move%20to%20threaten%20his%20neighbor%20after%20starting%20the%20year%20by%20eliminating%20the%20concept%20of%20peaceful%20unification%20from%20his%20state's%20national%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Korea%20has%20been%20under%20new%20pressure%20as%20South%20Korea%2C%20Japan%20and%20the%20US%20have%20raised%20their%20cooperation%20to%20new%20levels%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%20and%20stepped%20up%20military%20training%20against%20threats%20posed%20by%20Pyongyang.%20The%20US%20has%20also%20been%20bringing%20nuclear-capable%20military%20assets%20such%20as%20aircraft%20carrier%20groups%20and%20attack%20submarines%20off%20the%20Korean%20Peninsula%20in%20shows%20of%20force%20meant%20to%20deter%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20from%20aggression.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNorth%20Korea%20is%20nervous%20to%20the%20reinforced%20trilateral%20partnership%20between%20Seoul%2C%20Washington%20and%20Tokyo%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kak%20Soo%20Shin%2C%20a%20former%20career%20diplomat%20who%20once%20served%20as%20South%20Korea's%20ambassador%20to%20Japan.%20%26quot%3BIn%20a%20bid%20to%20drive%20a%20wedge%20in%20this%20strengthening%20ties%2C%20North%20Korea%20seems%20to%20make%20use%20of%20the%20prime%20minister's%20desire%20to%20open%20up%20a%20door%20to%20Pyongyang%26quot%3B%20adding%20this%20could%20help%20Kishida%20boost%20his%20low%20support%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShin%20sees%20little%20likelihood%20of%20a%20summit%20taking%20place%20given%20the%20differences%20on%20abductees%20and%20the%20thorny%20issue%20of%20North%20Korea's%20nuclear%20weapons%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20leader%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20also%20offered%20an%20olive%20branch%20when%20he%20sent%20a%20rare%20message%20to%20Kishida%20expressing%20sympathy%20and%20condolences%20for%20the%20victims%20of%20an%20earthquake%20in%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKishida%20has%20long%20said%20he%20is%20willing%20to%20meet%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20without%20preconditions.%20Last%20week%2C%20he%20said%20his%20government%20has%20made%20%26quot%3Bvarious%2C%20concrete%26quot%3B%20efforts%20for%20a%20summit%20with%20the%20aim%20to%20resolve%20the%20long-standing%20issue%20of%20Japanese%20abducted%20by%20North%20Korea%2C%20Kyodo%20News%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETokyo%20officially%20lists%2017%20of%20its%20citizens%20as%20having%20been%20abducted%20by%20North%20Korea%20in%20the%201970%20and%2080s%2C%20five%20of%20whom%20returned%20home%20in%202002.%20North%20Korea%20considers%20the%20issue%20settled%20and%20has%20blasted%20Japan%20for%20repeatedly%20raising%20it.%20North%20Korea%20claims%20that%20eight%20of%20the%20abductees%20have%20died%20and%20the%20other%20four%20were%20never%20in%20its%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%20statement%20from%20Kim%20Yo%20Jong%2C%20a%20senior%20US%20State%20Department%20official%20charged%20with%20managing%20issues%20with%20Pyongyang%20said%20Kishida%20has%20mentioned%20a%20summit%20before%20and%20Washington%20would%20support%20talks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20encourage%20any%20kind%20of%20dialogue%2C%26quot%3B%20Jung%20Pak%20said%20in%20an%20interview.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Korea%20has%20a%20habit%20of%20seeking%20concessions%20for%20engagement%20with%20countries%20it%20sees%20as%20adversaries%2C%20such%20as%20Japan.%20It%20has%20shunned%20offers%20over%20the%20past%20several%20years%20from%20the%20US%2C%20Japan%20and%20South%20Korea%20for%20talks%20and%20appears%20to%20be%20receiving%20significant%20support%20from%20Russia%20in%20recent%20months%20in%20return%20for%20arms%20sent%20by%20Kim's%20regime%20to%20help%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20in%20his%20war%20on%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202002%2C%20Junichiro%20Koizumi%20became%20the%20first%20Japanese%20prime%20minister%20to%20visit%20North%20Korea.%20Soon%20after%20that%2C%20five%20Japanese%20kidnapped%20by%20North%20Korean%20agents%20in%201978%20were%20reunited%20with%20their%20families%20after%20arriving%20in%20Tokyo.%20Koizumi%20and%20then%20North%20Korean%20leader%20Kim%20Jong%20Il%20also%20agreed%20to%20work%20to%20establish%20formal%20diplomatic%20relations%20but%20that%20never%20came%20to%20fruition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20Kim%20Yo%20Jong's%20invitation%20to%20Kishida%20comes%20with%20strings%20attached%20should%20have%20us%20question%20the%20sincerity%20of%20the%20DPRK's%20intentions%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Soo%20Kim%2C%20a%20former%20Korea%20analyst%20at%20the%20Central%20Intelligence%20Agency%20who%20now%20works%20at%20US-based%20management%20consulting%20firm%20LMI%2C%20referring%20to%20North%20Korea%20by%20its%20formal%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20to%20mention%2C%20the%20chasm%20in%20North%20Korea-Japan%20relations%20is%20quite%20wide%20%E2%80%94%20would%20thawing%20their%20relations%20be%20so%20simple%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708062360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fv1ln8tdg_kim-yo-jong-reuters-_625x300_11_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fkim-jo