s%20were%20briefed%20on%20its%20nature.%20It's%20still%20unclear%20if%20it%20would%20be%20nuclear-armed%20or%20nuclear-powered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20unlikely%20to%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bspace%20nuke%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20conventional%20sense.%20It's%20thought%20to%20be%20designed%20to%20attack%20satellites%2C%20not%20targets%20on%20Earth%20%E2%80%94%20a%20detail%20that%20White%20House%20national%20security%20spokesperson%20John%20Kirby%20confirmed%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fpress-briefings%2F2024%2F02%2F15%2Fpress-briefing-by-press-secretary-karine-jean-pierre-and-white-house-national-security-communications-advisor-john-kirby-3%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThursday%20press%20briefing.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20not%20talking%20about%20a%20weapon%20that%20can%20be%20used%20to%20attack%20human%20beings%20or%20cause%20physical%20destruction%20here%20on%20Earth%2C%26quot%3B%20Kirby%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20said%2C%20we've%20been%20closely%20monitoring%20this%20Russian%20activity%2C%20and%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20take%20it%20very%20seriously.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKirby%20added%20that%20the%20weapon%20is%20not%20an%20%26quot%3Bactive%20capability%26quot%3B%20and%20hasn't%20been%20deployed%2C%20aligning%20with%20reports%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F02%2F14%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fintelligence-russia-nuclear.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F02%2F14%2Fpolitics%2Fhouse-intel-chairman-serious-national-security-threat%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20is%20still%20in%20development.%20Both%20outlets%20cited%20US%20officials%20who%20were%20not%20named.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20though%20Russia's%20pursuit%20of%20this%20particular%20capability%20is%20troubling%2C%20there%20is%20no%20immediate%20threat%20to%20anyone's%20safety%2C%26quot%3B%20Kirby%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKirby%20didn't%20specify%20what%20nuclear%20capabilities%20the%20new%20weapon%20might%20possess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20nuclear%20energy%20can%20be%20used%20for%20propulsion%20in%20an%20engineering%20sense.%20It%20can%20also%20be%20used%20as%20a%20weapon%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20declined%20to%20elaborate%20when%20pressed%20by%20reporters.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20not%20prudent%20to%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Kirby%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20spokesperson%20also%20said%20the%20weapon%20would%20violate%20the%20Outer%20Space%20Treaty%20of%201967%2C%20of%20which%20Russia%20is%20still%20a%20participant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.armscontrol.org%2Ffactsheets%2Fouterspace%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%25201967%2520Outer%2520Space%2520Treaty%2Cexploration%2520and%2520use%2520of%2520space.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20treaty%20specifically%20bans%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20stationing%20of%20weapons%20of%20mass%20destruction%20in%20space%2C%20including%20nuclear%20arms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20Russia%20has%2C%20in%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20been%20pulling%20out%20of%20its%20past%20agreed-upon%20nuclear%20treaties%2C%20sparking%20concerns%20that%20it%20may%20usher%20in%20a%20new%20Cold%20War%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKirby%20said%20that%20if%20Russia%20ends%20its%20involvement%20in%20the%20Outer%20Space%20Treaty%2C%20the%20US%20doesn't%20intend%20to%20follow%20suit%20and%20violate%20the%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20a%20signatory%20to%20that%20treaty.%20We%20take%20our%20obligations%20under%20that%20treaty%20very%20seriously%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fspace-threat-assessment-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAn%20April%202023%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%20assessed%20that%20Russia%20is%20developing%20anti-satellite%20weapons%20but%20has%20not%20deployed%20them%20in%20its%20war%20against%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20relies%20heavily%20on%20Starlink%20satellites%20for%20its%20communications.%20The%20US%20also%20uses%20an%20extensive%20network%20of%20satellites%20to%20maintain%20military%20communications%20and%20control%20over%20its%20nuclear%20arsenal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntelligence%20on%20the%20new%20weapon%20became%20the%20subject%20of%20alarm%20in%20Capitol%20Hill%20on%20Wednesday%20when%20GOP%20House%20Intelligence%20Chairman%20Mike%20Turner%20issued%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fhomenews%2Fhouse%2F4468159-speaker-johnson-on-national-security-threat-there-is-no-need-for-public-alarm%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eurgent%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20calling%20lawmakers%20to%20hear%20about%20a%20%26quot%3Bnational%20security%20threat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20House%20representatives%20later%20released%20statements%20saying%20that%20the%20intel%20was%20no%20cause%20for%20panic%20and%20that%20it%20did%20not%20discuss%20an%20urgent%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227374%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20House%20Minority%20Leader%20Hakeem%20Jeffries%20arrives%20for%20an%20intelligence%20briefing%20by%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Jake%20Sullivan%20in%20the%20US%20Capitol%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20on%20February%2015%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ced248a610a9069d59a8cb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224916%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20House%20Minority%20Leader%20Hakeem%20Jeffries%20arrives%20for%20an%20intelligence%20briefing%20by%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Jake%20Sullivan%20in%20the%20US%20Capitol%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20on%20February%2015%2C%202024.%3Cp%3EMANDEL%20NGAN%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20going%20to%20ruin%20you