never%20static.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2022%2F09%2F06%2Fworld%2Fearliest-mammal-teeth-scn-scli-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Efirst%20mammals%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94small%2C%20shrew-like%20creatures%E2%80%94appeared%20around%20225%20million%20years%20ago.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20nearly%20all%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20land%20was%20connected%20together%20into%20a%20single%2C%20giant%20landmass%2C%20a%20supercontinent%20we%20call%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dvb_TnPD9TRU%5C%22%3EPangaea%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Around%20180%20million%20years%20ago%2C%20Pangea%20began%20to%20break%20up%2C%20drifting%20into%20continents%20somewhat%20more%20familiar%20to%20us%20today.%20As%20the%20climate%20kept%20on%20fluctuating%2C%20new%20organisms%20continuously%20arose%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20were%20much%20better%20at%20digesting%20the%20woody%20trunks%20of%20trees%2C%20rotting%20them%20away%20and%20thus%20curtailing%20newer%20formations%20of%20coal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20while%20dinosaurs%20still%20tromped%20happily%20across%20insular%20India%2C%20volcanoes%20began%20to%20belch%20as%20the%20Indian%20plate%20crossed%20over%20%E2%80%98hot%20spots%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20mantle.%20But%20following%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20Chicxulub%20meteor%20on%20the%20opposite%20side%20of%20the%20globe%2C%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fscience-nature%2Fmeteorite-killed-dinosaurs-also-triggered-underwater-volcanoes-180968106%2F%5C%22%3Evolcanoes%20boomed%20into%20overdrive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20burying%20most%20of%20the%20island%20in%20lava%20and%20spewing%20massive%20quantities%20of%20gas%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20over%20the%20next%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.aac7549%5C%22%3Ehalf%20a%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20This%20extreme%2C%20prolonged%20environmental%20disruption%20likely%20compounded%20and%20extended%20the%20extinction%20event%20triggered%20by%20the%20meteor%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20reptiles%20had%20grown%20gigantic.%20Dinosaurs%2C%20in%20their%20various%20forms%2C%20great%20and%20small%2C%20remained%20the%20dominant%20beasts%20on%20land%20for%20250%20million%20years.%20Their%20heyday%20only%20ended%2C%20one%20fine%20day%20about%2066%20million%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20the%20giant%20Chicxulub%20meteor%20crashed%20into%20the%20sea.%20The%20heat%20of%20the%20collision%20instantly%20incinerated%20large%20swathes%20of%20the%20planet%E2%80%99s%20surface.%20Fire%20and%20rocky%20debris%20rained%20down%20upon%20the%20land.%20The%20impact%20unleashed%20a%20mega-tsunami%20with%20waves%20hundreds%20of%20meters%20high.%20It%20forced%20a%20seismic%20response%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.berkeley.edu%2F2015%2F04%2F30%2Fdid-dinosaur-killing-asteroid-trigger-largest-lava-flows-on-earth%5C%22%3Ecaused%20swarms%20of%20volcanoes%3C%2Fa%3E%20around%20the%20globe%20to%20belch%20and%20spurt%20continuously%20for%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20years%2C%20burying%20millions%20of%20kilometres%20of%20land%20under%20burning%20lava%E2%80%94and%20shaping%20the%20geography%20of%20many%20lands%2C%20including%20the%20Deccan%20Plateau.%20This%20magnitude%20of%20devastation%20once%20again%20utterly%20revised%20life%20on%20Earth%2C%20in%20what%E2%80%99s%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20Fifth%20Great%20Mass%20Extinction%20Event%E2%80%94the%20fifth%20time%20that%20most%20species%20then%20existing%20on%20Earth%20rapidly%20died%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20before%2C%20life%20eventually%20bounced%20back%20with%20even%20greater%20diversity.%20New%20mixes%20of%20forests%20grew.%20Birds%20now%20filled%20the%20skies.%20By%20forty%20million%20years%20ago%2C%20mammals%20were%20emerging%20as%20the%20most%20dominant%20class%20of%20creature%20on%20land%2C%20spreading%20themselves%20under%20steamy%20jungle%20canopies%20around%20the%20planet%2C%20some%20even%20sliding%20back%20into%20the%20oceans%2C%20evolving%20into%20whales%20and%20dolphins.%20This%20exuberant%20flowering%20of%20life%20was%20not%20quelled%20even%20as%20the%20planet%20embarked%20upon%20yet%20another%20cooling%20trend.%20Snow%20began%20to%20fall%20again%20after%20many%20millions%20of%20years%2C%20first%20in%20the%20mountains%20of%20Antarctica.%20Over%20the%20following%20millions%20of%20years%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20highest%20peaks%2C%20north%20and%20south%2C%20slowly%20donned%20mantles%20of%20ice.%20Earth%20had%20been%20encrusted%20in%20ice%20before%2C%20but%20not%20when%20it%20was%20also%20adorned%20by%20forests%20and%20grasslands%20swarming%20with%20legions%20of%20warm-blooded%20creatures%2C%20birds%20and%20mammals%2C%20amid%20the%20richest%2C%20densest%2C%20most%20diverse%20biota%20it%20had%20ever%20created.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20cooling%2C%20drying%20climate%2C%20some%20forests%20in%20Africa%20were%20burning%20away%20into%20grasslands.%20It%20was%20then%20that%20our%20earliest%20hominid%20ancestors%E2%80%94two-legged%20apes%20of%20short%20stature%E2%80%94climbed%20down%20from%20their%20shrinking%20tree%20cover%20and%20strode%20onto%20the%20African%20savannas%2C%20some%20six%20million%20years%20ago.%20Like%20other%20primates%2C%20they%20probably%20used%20some%20tools%2C%20such%20as%20digging%20sticks.%20But%20over%20the%20next%20few%20million%20years%2C%20as%20their%20cognitive%20capacities%20were%20reshaped%20by%20their%20changing%20environment%2C%20they%20began%20noticing%20the%20properties%20of%20different%20types%20of%20stone%2C%20how%20best%20to%20break%20them%20into%20shapes%20useful%20for%20chopping%20things.%20They%20also%20came%20to%20understand%20some%20things%20about%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExtreme%20vulcanism%20across%20insular%20India%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Cretaceous%20Period%20contributed%20to%20the%20mass%20extinction%20event%20that%20ended%20the%20dinosaurs%E2%80%99%20reign.%20The%20resulting%20lava%20beds%20remain%20major%20geologic%20features%20across%20much%20of%20peninsular%20India.%20Today%20called%20the%20Deccan%20Traps%2C%20they%20still%20rank%20among%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.geoscienceworld.org%2Fgsa%2Fgsabulletin%2Farticle-abstract%2F127%2F11-12%2F1507%2F126064%2FTriggering-of-the-largest-Deccan-eruptions-by-the%3FredirectedFrom%3Dfulltext%5C%22%3Emost%20extensive%20and%20voluminous%3C%2Fa%3E%20lava%20fields%20known%20on%20Earth.%20Some%20sixty-six%20million%20years%20later%2C%20people%20would%20carve%20Buddhist%20monasteries%20and%20Hindu%20temples%20into%20their%20cliff%20faces%20at%20Ajanta%20and%20Ellora.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20two%20million%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20massive%20fields%20of%20ice%20had%20well%20taken%20hold%20of%20Antarctica%20and%20the%20far%20northern%20latitudes%2C%20our%20early%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faustralian.museum%2Flearn%2Fscience%2Fhuman-evolution%2Fhominid-and-hominin-whats-the-difference%2F%5C%22%3Ehominin%3C%2Fa%3E%20ancestor%2C%20%3Cem%3EHomo%20erectus%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20had%20become%20recognisably%20human%2C%20though%20not%20quite%20identical%20to%20us%20(we%2C%20%3Cem%3EHomo%20sapiens%20sapiens%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20appeared%20a%20mere%20three%20hundred%20thousand%20years%20ago).%20With%20their%20well-developed%20stone%20tools%20and%20mastery%20of%20fire%2C%20%3Cem%3EH.%20erectus%3C%2Fem%3E%20ventured%20beyond%20Africa%2C%20eventually%20colonizing%20much%20of%20southern%20Eurasia%20from%20what%20today%20is%20Spain%20to%20India%20to%20China%20and%20the%20farthest%20reaches%20of%20peninsular%20southeast%20Asia%20(which%20would%20later%20become%20the%20islands%20of%20Indonesia).%20None%20of%20what%20followed%20would%20have%20been%20possible%20without%20both%20fire%20and%20a%20propensity%20to%20build%20thick%20social%20worlds%2C%20two%20aspects%20of%20being%20human%20that%20appear%20tightly%20linked%20and%20are%20the%20subject%20of%20the%20next%20essay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUsha%20Alexander%20trained%20in%20science%20and%20anthropology.%20After%20working%20for%20years%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20she%20now%20lives%20in%20Gurugram.%20She%E2%80%99s%20written%20two%20novels%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Legend%20of%20Virinara%3Cem%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EOnly%20the%20Eyes%20Are%20Mine%3Cem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707996634000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15155616%2FPandavFalls06.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fa-planetary-perspective%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Earth%20was%20born%20about%20four%20and%20a%20half%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20alongside%20several%20sibling%20planets%2C%20all%20of%20them%20formed%20from%20fragments%20of%20material%20left%20over%20after%20the%20birth%20of%20the%20Sun.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fa-planetary-perspective%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Domino's%20worker%20filmed%20picking%20their%20nose%20-%20and%20wiping%20finger%20on%20dough%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707995280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F21%2F08%2F70x70%2Fskynews-dominos-pizza_5466630.jpg%3F20210803083640%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fdominos-pizza-apologises-after-employee-nose-picking-video-goes-viral-13072129%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Domino's%20Pizza%20has%20apologised%20after%20a%20video%20of%20an%20employee%20appearing%20to%20pick%20his%20nose%20and%20wipe%20his%20hand%20on%20dough%20went%20viral.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A69%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fdominos-pizza-apologises-after-employee-nose-picking-video-goes-viral-13072129%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fdominos-pizza-apologises-after-employee-nose-picking-video-goes-viral-13072129%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fdominos-pizza-apologises-after-employee-nose-picking-video-goes-viral-13072129%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Meaty%20rice'%20has%20just%20been%20invented%20-%20scientists%20say%20it%20can%20have%20big%20benefits%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707994200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F70x70%2Fskynews-beef-rice-lab-grown-meat_6456327.jpg%3F20240215103555%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fscientists-create-meaty-rice-with-extra-protein-13072053%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Scientists%20in%20South%20Korea%20have%20grown%20beef%20cells%20inside%20grains%20of%20rice%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20create%20food%20that%20is%20cheaper%20and%20more%20eco-friendly%20than%20real%20cuts%20of%20meat.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A92%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fscientists-create-meaty-rice-with-extra-protein-13072053%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fscientists-create-meaty-rice-with-extra-protein-13072053%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fscientists-create-meaty-rice-with-extra-protein-13072053%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Part%20of%20Secret%20Ballot'%3A%20How%20the%20Modi%20Govt%20Backed%20Electoral%20Bonds%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F10170626%2Fsyed-hussaini-HlLno-CSbq8-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20February%2015%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-quash-anonymous%5C%22%3Epronounced%20electoral%20bonds%20unconstitutional%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20in%202018%20and%20allowed%20anonymous%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%20To%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20heard%20pleas%20against%20the%20bonds%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20spoke%20of%20its%20justification%20for%20the%20scheme%20%E2%80%93%20one%20which%20the%20court%20has%20now%20held%20as%20violative%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20written%20submission%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20had%20said%20that%20citizens%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20know%20must%20be%20balanced%20with%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20privacy%20while%20donating%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20maintained%20that%20the%20citizens%20did%20not%20have%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgeneral%20right%20to%20know%20regarding%20the%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20emphasised%20that%20%E2%80%98right%20to%20know%E2%80%99%20itself%20is%20not%20a%20general%20right%20available%20to%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20argued%20against%20the%20court%20examining%20the%20%E2%80%9Cinfluence%20of%20contributions%20by%20companies%20to%20political%20parties%E2%80%9D%2C%20calling%20it%20an%20issue%20of%20democratic%20significance%20that%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cbest%20left%20to%20the%20legislature.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Union%20also%20asked%20the%20court%20to%20exercise%20judicial%20restraint%20citing%20the%20legislation%E2%80%99s%20connection%20to%20economic%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20contended%20that%20the%20right%20of%20a%20buyer%20to%20purchase%20electoral%20bonds%20without%20having%20to%20disclose%20their%20political%20preferences%20ensured%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20privacy.%20The%20Union%20also%20told%20the%20court%20that%20%E2%80%9Canonymous%20political%20donations%E2%80%9D%20were%20a%20part%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20concept%20of%20secret%20ballot%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20claimed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cdonating%20money%20to%20one%E2%80%99s%20preferred%20party%20is%20a%20form%20of%20political%20self-expression%20that%20lies%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20privacy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20Union%20did%20not%20distinguish%20between%20individuals%20and%20corporations%20while%20arguing%20for%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20of%20citizens%20while%20buying%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%5C%22%3EElectoral%20Bonds%20Are%20Illegal%20Now.%20But%20Who%20Benefitted%20for%20the%206%2B%20Years%20They%20Lasted%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20fact%20that%20one%20party%20has%20received%20more%20support%20through%20donations%20than%20other%20parties%20cannot%20in%20itself%20be%20the%20legal%20grounds%20to%20challenge%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20government%20told%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20has%20been%20the%20net%20gainer%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme.%20Of%20the%20total%20number%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2012%2C008%20crore%20sold%20between%202017-2018%20and%202022-2023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%5C%22%3Ethe%20BJP%20received%20nearly%2055%25%20or%20Rs%206%2C564%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Congress%20has%20received%20just%209.5%25%20of%20all%20bonds%20sold%20in%20the%20five-year%20period%20at%20Rs%201%2C135%20crore.%20The%20Trinamool%20Congress%20has%20received%20Rs%201%2C096%20crore%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20this%20same%20time%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%2C%20while%20rejecting%20the%20Union%E2%80%99s%20argument%20in%20favour%20of%20exercising%20judicial%20restraint%20on%20account%20of%20the%20legislation%20being%20a%20part%20of%20%E2%80%9Ceconomic%20policy%E2%80%9D%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20court%20does%20not%20rely%20on%20ipse%20dixit%20%5Bassertion%5D%20of%20the%20government%2C%20that%20a%20legislation%20is%20an%20economic%20legislation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20amendment%20to%20Section%2031%20of%20the%20RBI%20Act%20can%20be%20classified%20as%20a%20financial%20provision%E2%80%A6%20However%2C%20any%20resemblance%20to%20an%20economic%20policy%20ends%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20amendment%20in%20question%20fall%20under%20the%20following%20two%20heads%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20Non-disclosure%20of%20information%20on%20electoral%20financing%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn2.%20Provisions%20permitting%20unlimited%20corporate%20funding%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20both%20accounts%2C%20the%20legislation%20relates%20to%20the%20electoral%20process%2C%20the%20court%20said%20as%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-quash-anonymous%5C%22%3Edeclared%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20as%20unconstitutional%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20verdict%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707993917000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F10170626%2Fsyed-hussaini-HlLno-CSbq8-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpart-of-secret-ballot-how-the-modi-govt-backed-electoral-bonds-in-the-supreme-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20government%20had%20claimed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cdonating%20money%20to%20one%E2%80%99s%20preferred%20party%20is%20a%20form%20of%20political%20self-expression%20that%20lies%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20privacy%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A42%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpart-of-secret-ballot-how-the-modi-govt-backed-electoral-bonds-in-the-supreme-court%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Survey%20Finds%20Deep%20Economic%20Discontent%2C%20Job%20Pessimism%3B%2052%25%20Say%20Modi's%20Policies%20Favour%20'Big%20Business'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15143525%2Fkevin-john-Q6FUBxz7HF8-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20thing%20to%20note%20in%20the%20first%20%E2%80%98Mood%20of%20the%20Nation%E2%80%99%20poll%20of%202024%20is%20a%20majority%20of%20those%20surveyed%20%E2%80%93%2064%25%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20substantial%20number%20of%20people%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20report%20that%20their%20economic%20situation%20has%20deteriorated%20or%20remained%20the%20same%20in%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20under%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20seamless%20regime%20with%20a%20clear%20majority.%20Over%20one-third%2C%2035%25%2C%20say%20their%20situation%20has%20got%20worse%20relative%20to%20what%20what%20it%20was%20in%202014.%20This%20is%20one%20apiece%20with%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20consumer%20confidence%20surveys%2C%20which%20have%20been%20noting%20the%20despondent%20mood%20amongst%20those%20surveyed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Fexplainspeaking-consumer-sentiments-improving-but-still-stuck-in-pessimism-9160505%2F%5C%22%3Ethrough%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20second%20term%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20starting%20from%202019%2C%20well%20before%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20India%20Today%20Mood%20of%20the%20Nation%20poll%2C%20which%20brings%20out%20the%20economic%20discontent%20and%20restlessness%20vividly%2C%20was%20conducted%20by%20CVoter.%20The%20survey%20has%2035%2C801%20respondents%2C%20reached%20out%20through%20computer%20assisted%20telephone%20interviews%20(CATI)%20between%20December%2015%2C%202023%20and%20January%2028%2C%202024%2C%20with%20the%20interviews%20covering%20all%20Lok%20Sabha%20segments%20across%20all%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnemployment%20%E2%80%9Cserious%E2%80%9D%3A%2071%25%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20unemployment%2C%2071%25%20say%20the%20situation%20is%20either%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20serious%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cserious%E2%80%9D.%20A%20whopping%2054%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20say%20the%20jobs%20situation%20is%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20serious%E2%80%9D.%20Objective%20data%20on%20the%20state%20of%20unemployment%2C%20despite%20government%20denials%2C%20has%20pointed%20to%20a%20sad%20state%20of%20affairs%2C%20leading%20to%20even%20a%20controversial%20withholding%20of%20employment%20data%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20with%20the%20government%20agreeing%20to%20release%20the%20bad%20news%20only%20after%20the%202019%20general%20elections%20were%20over.%20This%20led%20to%20two%20resignations%20from%20the%20National%20Statistical%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20541px)%2085vw%2C%20541px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15140808%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-1.58.44%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22541%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15140808%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-1.58.44%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201104w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15140808%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-1.58.44%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x270.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15140808%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-1.58.44%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x920.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697299%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22487%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20quality%20of%20jobs%20has%20also%20been%20a%20point%20of%20distress%2C%20with%20formal%20employment%20going%20down.%20State%20jobs%20or%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ebhartis%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20have%20been%20postponed%20for%20years%20on%20end%20with%20an%20entire%20generation%20preparing%20for%20%E2%80%98competitive%20examinations%E2%80%99%20feeling%20left%20out%20and%20out%20of%20a%20job.%20The%20Armed%20Forces%20deciding%20to%20move%20towards%20an%20%E2%80%98Agniveer%E2%80%99%20model%20of%20hiring%20soldiers%2C%20or%20short-term%20contract%20soldiering%20wholly%20replacing%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20soldier%20as%20a%20job%20providing%20respect%2C%20regular%20income%20and%20purpose%20has%20hit%20avenues%20for%20jobs%20for%20youngsters%2C%20with%20consequences%20in%20a%20demographic%20where%20the%20median%20age%20in%20India%20is%20around%2030%20years.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fstatistics%2F254469%2Fmedian-age-of-the-population-in-india%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520median%2520age%2520in%2520India%2C50.4%2520years%2520old%2520by%25202100.%5C%22%3EStatista%2C%20(as%20there%20has%20been%20no%20Census%20since%202011%3C%2Fa%3E)%20says%20it%20was%C2%A0a%20median%20of%2032.4%20years%20old%C2%A0in%202020%2C%20meaning%20that%20half%20the%20population%20is%20older%20than%20that%2C%20and%20the%20other%20half%20younger.%20Lower%20median%20ages%20need%20more%20job%20making.%20This%20figure%20was%20lowest%20in%201970%2C%20at%2017.3%20years%2C%20by%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CCurrent%20Household%20Expenses%E2%80%9D%20out%20of%20whack%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCurrent%20household%20expenses%20are%20difficult%20to%20manage%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20this%20worries%2062%25%20of%20those%20surveyed.%20If%20you%20add%20those%20who%20worry%20about%20raised%20expenses%20but%20still%20say%20it%20is%20manageable%20(33%25)%2C%20this%20makes%20price%20rise%20a%20concern%20for%2095%25%20of%20those%20surveyed.%20This%20is%20the%20highest%20metric%20number%20logged%20for%20any%20question%20across%20the%20survey.%20A%20total%20of%2066%25%20say%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20their%20household%20incomes%20will%20rise.%2030%25%20feel%20it%20will%20deteriorate.%20Price%20inflation%20is%20the%20biggest%20failure%20of%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20says%2026%25%20of%20the%20cohort%20surveyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20real%20numbers%20go%2C%20prices%20have%20been%20astronomical%2C%20and%20been%20well%20out%20of%20the%20RBI%20band%20of%20acceptable%20rates%20(between%204%20to%206%25)%20for%20some%20time%20now.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbusiness%2FEconomy%2Fretail-inflation-eases-to-51-in-january-a-3-month-low%2Farticle67838256.ece%5C%22%3EIn%20latest%20figures%20in%20for%20January%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20food%20inflation%20is%20still%20high%2C%20at%208.3%25%20compared%20with%209.5%25%20in%20December%202023.%20The%20retail%20inflation%20is%20at%205.1%25%20in%20January%2C%20but%20has%20been%20hovering%20well%20above%20that%3B%20it%20was%205.7%25%20a%20month%20earlier.%20For%20urban%20India%2C%20food%20inflation%20is%20at%209%25.%20It%20was%20at%2010.4%25%20in%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20521px)%2085vw%2C%20521px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15142546%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-2.06.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22521%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15142546%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-2.06.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15142546%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-2.06.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x270.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15142546%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-2.06.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x922.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697303%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22468%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%E2%80%99s%20consumer%20confidence%20surveys%20bear%20out%20the%20anxiety%20among%20households%20over%20inflation.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rbi.org.in%2FScripts%2FPublicationsView.aspx%3Fid%3D22422%5C%22%3EThe%20latest%20data%2C%20released%20on%20February%208%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20records%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmajority%20of%20survey%20participants%20expect%20a%20rise%20in%20price%20and%20inflationary%20pressures%20especially%20for%20food%20product%20category%20for%20the%20three%20months%20horizon%E2%80%9D.%20They%20say%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmedian%20inflation%20expectation%20for%20the%20three%20months%20ahead%20increased%20by%2010%20bps%20and%20stood%20at%209.2%20per%20cent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%E2%80%99s%20Michael%20Debabrata%20Patra%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rbi.org.in%2FScripts%2FBS_PressReleaseDisplay.aspx%3Fprid%3D56982%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20December%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Cinflation%20remains%20highly%20vulnerable%20to%20food%20price%20spikes%2C%20as%20the%20spurt%20in%20momentum%20in%20daily%20data%20on%20key%20food%20items%20for%20the%20month%20of%20November%20and%20early%20December%20reveal%E2%80%9D.%20He%20emphasised%20that%20%E2%80%9Chouseholds%20are%20already%20wary%3A%20although%20they%20expect%20inflation%20to%20remain%20unchanged%20three%20months%20ahead%2C%20they%20are%20more%20unsure%20about%20this%20prognosis%20than%20they%20were%20two%20months%20ago.%20Over%20the%20year%20ahead%2C%20however%2C%20they%20are%20more%20sure%20than%20in%20the%20past%20that%20inflation%20will%20likely%20rise.%E2%80%9D%20Patra%20added%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cconsumers%20too%20reveal%20more%20pessimism%20about%20inflation%20a%20year%20ahead%20than%20when%20they%20were%20surveyed%20in%20September%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20say%20policies%20promote%20K-shaped%20growth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20brings%20out%20the%20belief%20in%20the%20past%20ten%20years%20that%20economic%20policies%20are%20being%20drawn%20up%20to%20help%20big%20business.%20A%20majority%20of%20people%20surveyed%2C%2052%25%2C%20say%20so.%20Only%209%25%20think%20economic%20policies%20are%20benefitting%20farmers%2C%2011%25%20are%20of%20the%20view%20they%20support%20small%20business%20and%20only%208%25%20say%20they%20benefit%20the%20salaried%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20economic%20policies%20have%20ended%20up%20widening%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20rich%20and%20the%20poor%2C%20is%20the%20feeling%20of%20nearly%20half%20of%20those%20surveyed.%20About%2045%25%20feel%20that%20the%20gap%20has%20got%20wider.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20468px)%2085vw%2C%20468px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15155900%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-3.55.54%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22468%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15155900%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-3.55.54%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201056w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15155900%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-3.55.54%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x290.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15155900%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-3.55.54%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x991.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697331%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22453%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20analysis%20by%20India%20Ratings%20and%20Research%20for%20FY22%20and%20FY23%2C%20cited%20by%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Cshows%20that%20wages%20for%20lower-income%20groups%2C%20comprising%20agricultural%20rural%20workers%20and%20unskilled%20workers%2C%20saw%20degrowth%20or%20negligible%20wage%20growth%2C%20if%20at%20all.%20In%20contrast%2C%20wages%20for%20corporates%2C%20representing%20the%20top%2050%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20income%20bracket%2C%20increased%20by%20over%2010%20per%20cent%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years.%E2%80%9D%20The%20political%20landscape%20has%20been%20dominated%20by%20conversation%20over%20one%20business%20house%2C%20the%20Adani%20Group%E2%80%99s%20rapid%20growth%2C%20which%20continued%20also%20through%20the%20pandemic%2C%20far%20outstripping%20the%20rate%20of%20growth%20in%20India%20and%20also%20growth%20of%20its%20peers%20in%20the%20business%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBig%20corporations%20as%20a%20group%20have%20benefitted%20from%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20policies%2C%20says%20a%20look%20at%20taxes%20paid%20by%20them%2C%20as%20compared%20to%20what%20individuals%20pay.%20The%20government%20has%20been%20boasting%20about%20this.%20The%20government%20data%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fincome-tax-filers-more-than-double-to-77-8-million-in-10-years-govt-data-124012300845_1.html%5C%22%3Eas%20released%20by%20the%20Central%20Board%20of%20Direct%20Taxes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20CBDT%20says%20that%20the%20number%20of%20tax%20payers%20filing%20income%20tax%20returns%20has%20more%20than%20doubled%20to%207.78%20crore%20in%20the%20past%2010%20years.%20But%20this%20%E2%80%98data%E2%80%99%20conceals%20a%20bigger%20story%20that%20has%20implications%20on%20economic%20equality%20statistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20only%20thrice%20since%20the%201990s%20that%20individuals%20have%20paid%20more%20than%20corporations%20as%20tax.%20The%20first%20was%20in%201991-92%2C%20then%20in%202020-21%20and%20now.%20Economic%20commentator%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fprofits-for-corporates-taxes-for-individuals-2889682%5C%22%3EVivek%20Kaul%20cites%3C%2Fa%3E%20aggregate%20data%20of%2035%2C000%20companies%20sourced%20from%20the%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy%20(CMIE)%20which%20%E2%80%9Csuggests%20that%20profit-before-tax%20(PBT)%20of%20these%20companies%20went%20up%20144%25%20between%202018-19%20and%202021-22.%20Plus%2C%20the%20tax%20provisions%20went%20up%20just%2039%25%2C%20helping%20push%20up%20profit-after-tax%20(PAT)%20by%20244%25.%E2%80%9D%20The%20government%20had%20cut%20corporate%20tax%20rate%20in%20September%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20points%20out%20to%20how%20this%20inhibits%20private%20consumption%20growth%20in%202023-24%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20be%204.4%25%2C%20the%20slowest%20since%202002-03%2C%20except%20for%20the%20pandemic%20year.%20As%20private%20consumption%20forms%2057%25%20of%20the%20Indian%20economy%2C%20the%20government%20could%20have%20slashed%20personal%20income%20tax%20rates%20in%20the%20interim%20budget%2C%20and%20encouraged%20people%20to%20spend%20more%20and%20drive%20consumption.%20But%20with%20the%20fall%20in%20corporate%20tax%20collections%2C%20it%20cannot%20do%20that.%20There%20is%20a%20huge%20and%20continued%20cess%20on%20petrol%20and%20fuel%2C%20despite%20a%20long%20span%20when%20oil%20prices%20were%20at%20record%20low%20levels%2C%20as%20none%20of%20the%20benefits%20were%20passed%20on%20to%20consumers.%20This%20is%20also%20an%20indirect%2C%20regressive%20tax%2C%20hurting%20those%20at%20the%20lower%20end%20of%20the%20income%20scale%20more%20acutely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20by%20the%20%E2%80%98Mood%20of%20the%20Nation%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20people%20have%20caught%20on%20to%20how%20policies%20are%20hurting%20those%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20scale%20disproportionately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Economic%20Advisor%2C%20V.%20Anantha%20Nageswaran%20says%20today%20in%20a%20piece%20in%20%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CBy%20May%2C%20we%20will%20have%20learnt%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20economy%20has%20grown%20by%20more%20than%207%25%20annually%20in%20real%20terms%20over%20the%20last%20three%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707993011000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15143525%2Fkevin-john-Q6FUBxz7HF8-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fsurvey-finds-deep-economic-discontent-job-pessimism-52-say-modis-policies-favour-big-business%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20first%20%E2%80%98Mood%20of%20the%20Nation%E2%80%99%20poll%20of%2020